tool.name: scalecomparison

param.name: Filter
param.dialogReference:
The image filter used to process the sample block.

  • Median: Replaces each cell in the sample block with the median of the cells in the surrounding neighborhood, where the size of the neighborhood is determined by scale.

  • Minimum:Replaces each cell in the sample block with the minimum of the cells in the surrounding neighborhood.

  • Maximum:Replaces each cell in the sample block with the maximum of the cells in the surrounding neighborhood.

  • Percentile: Replaces each cell in the sample block with the the value below which a percentage of values in the surrounding neighborhood fall. The percentage is specified by the value of the Percentile parameter.

param.name: Percentile
param.dialogReference: The percentage used in the percentile image filter. Required only if the percentile image filter is used.
param.pythonReference: The percentage used in the percentile image filter. Required only if the percentile image filter is used.

param.name: Minimum Neighborhood_Size
param.dialogReference: The lower limit of the range of scales that will be processed. Determines the size of the neighborhood of cells that will be passed to the image filter function when calculating the value of each cell in the result image.
param.pythonReference: The lower limit of the range of scales that will be processed. Determines the size of the neighborhood of cells that will be passed to the image filter function when calculating the value of each cell in the result image.

param.name: Maximum Neighborhood_Size
param.dialogReference:
The upper limit of the range of scales that will be processed. Determines the size of the neighborhood of cells that will be passed to the image filter function when calculating the value of each cell in the result image.

Note: Depending on the capabilities of your machine, a large neighborhood size may cause the tool to fail due to excess memory usage.
param.pythonReference:

Note: Depending on the capabilities of your machine, a large neighborhood size may cause the tool to fail due to excess memory usage.

param.name: Comparison Location
param.dialogReference: The lower left-hand corner X and Y coordinate, in map units, of the window to be analyzed. The tool will construct a 200x200 cell selection starting from this location. If this value is ommitted, the window will be taken from the lower left-hand corner of the overall raster, which may not contain data in an irregular grid.

param.name: Output Filename
param.dialogReference: The path to which the resulting image will be saved. Supports saving to PNG, PDF, PS and SVG files.
param.pythonReference: The path to which the resulting image will be saved. Supports saving to PNG, PDF, PS and SVG files.

tool.summary: Processes a small sample of the input raster with a specified filter at up to 25 different scales and displays all results in a single image for quick and easy visual comparison.
tool.usage:
• Provides an easy way to qualitatively evaluate the usefulness of up to 25 different scales of analysis at once.

  • A specified image filter is used to process a 200 x 200 block of cells, starting from the bottom left corner of the input raster at a number of scales within the specified range. The results are then saved using the specified file name in a labeled array for easy inspection.

  • The resulting image can help you quickly decide at what scales further analysis with other BTM tools (such as Depth Statistics or Terrain Ruggedness (VRM)) would be most useful.

  • In this case, scale is synonymous with the size of the square neighborhood of cells that is passed to the filter function to calculate a value for each cell in the result image. The scales at which the sample block will be processed are chosen to be evenly distributed between the minimum and maximum neighborhood sizes specified.
